    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "Given reactions are<br><br>$$[P]\\buildrel {B{r_2}} \\over\n \\longrightarrow {C_2}{H_4}B{r_2}\\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{N{H_3}}^{NaN{H_2}}} [Q]$$<br><br>$$[Q]\\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{H{g^{2 + }},\\Delta }^{20\\% /{H_2}S{O_4}}} [R]\\buildrel {Zn - Hg/HCl} \\over\n \\longrightarrow [S]$$<br><br>[P] is an alkene with two carbon atoms i.e. ethene. When it reacts with Br<sub>2</sub>, addition reaction occurs and C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>Br<sub>2</sub> is formed.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hvyte7/140a85b4-9753-40c1-86f6-2b5a338be897/af400df0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvyte8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hvyte7/140a85b4-9753-40c1-86f6-2b5a338be897/af400df0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvyte8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 7 English Explanation 1\"><br>C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>Br<sub>2</sub> (1, 2-dibromoethane) on reaction with NaNH<sub>2</sub>/NH<sub>3</sub> gives ethyne (C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>).<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hvybha/01b8746a-3f14-47eb-a6a4-8d7d397a0e7b/a1696be0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvybhb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hvybha/01b8746a-3f14-47eb-a6a4-8d7d397a0e7b/a1696be0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvybhb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 7 English Explanation 2\"><br>Ethyne [Q] in presence of 20% H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>, Hg<sup>2+</sup> at 333 K gives ethanal.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hvxuju/094af719-9acc-47a2-b41c-c1d34a6cabf1/9455a4a0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvxujv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hvxuju/094af719-9acc-47a2-b41c-c1d34a6cabf1/9455a4a0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvxujv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 7 English Explanation 3\"><br>Ethanal [R] undergoes reduction in presence of Zn-Hg/HCl to give ethane [S]<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8hvxge6/c61a51cc-c944-4966-a8cf-1d38d9bb5158/8965f5e0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvxge7.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8hvxge6/c61a51cc-c944-4966-a8cf-1d38d9bb5158/8965f5e0-3d1d-11ed-8a57-433cdd4ead62/file-1l8hvxge7.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2018 Chemistry - Aldehyde and Ketone Question 7 English Explanation 4\">",
